African leaders called for intensified effrots to combat platic polution, coastal erosion and illegal fishing during the #OneOceanSummit in France. Presidents Hage Geingob from Namibia, Nana Akufo-Addo from Ghana and Samia Suluhu Hassan from Tanzania as well as Moroccan Prime Minister Aziz Akhannouch were among the 30 world leaders taking part in the meeting from February 9 to 12. Currently, plastic debris is the most abundant type of litter in the ocean, making up 80% of all marine debris found from surface waters to deep-sea sediments.